        "timestamp": "2019-01-23 09:42:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> I'm wondering why this race condition doesn't appear during my S3P\n > test in Casablanca. Maybe this is only happens on windows OS?\n > \n > @Ram, how can we reproduce the race condition you met? I'd like to\n > try this on linux\n\nSure, try the below steps.\n1) First remove the method that I have added to handle race condition in FileSystemReceptionHandler.\n2) Run the policy-distribution component using FileSystemReceptionHandler.\n3) Copy a CSAR file in the watch directory.\n4) Let the flow happen and policy creation is done in PDP.\n5) Delete the file from the watch directory.\n6) Copy the file again.\nThen you should be able to see the magic :)\nIf not, try the same in windows environment.",
        "patchset_number": 3
